last_episode_to_air.name: Rodent Rebellion: A Game of Cat and Rat (4)

name: The Garfield Show
overview: Your favorite lazy, fat cat is at it again. Garfield, Odie, Jon and the rest of the gang are back for more funny misadventures. Whether he's scarfing down lasagna or tricking Nermal the kitten, Garfield is guaranteed to crack you up. But remember: He hates Mondays!

episodes.name: Pasta Wars
episodes.overview: It's Garfield's birthday and Jon forgets. He later remembers, and makes 8 lasagnas but is one short. Meanwhile, an unusual type of Alien which looks like lasagna and can speak English with an Italian accent arrives on Earth. They plan to invade the Earth, but are quickly scared away by Garfield's ravenous appetite.

episodes.name: Mother Garfield
episodes.overview: A Bluebird gets trapped in Garfield's neighbor's garage leaving her eggs abandoned, forcing Garfield to look after them. The eggs hatch, and call Garfield mother. This episode marks the first appearance of Garfield's rival Harry, who is determined to eat the chicks.

episodes.name: Orange and Black
episodes.overview: Garfield disguises himself as "Catzilla" for Halloween, but people mistake him for the real Catzilla, a deadly creature who escaped from the zoo.

episodes.name: Freaky Monday
episodes.overview: Garfield and Odie get their bodies swapped by a Saturnian alien when it finds out Odie is tormented by Garfield. Odie wanders off to all the people who hate Garfield without knowing they will hurt him so Garfield must protect his body from the neighborhood dogs, Herman Post and the Chef.

episodes.name: Bone Diggers
episodes.overview: Odie digs up some bones and finds that they are from the very rare Brachiosaurus. Garfield tries to sell them to the local museum, but the museum curator instead wants to compulsory purchase and demolish Jon's house to search for more dinosaur bones.

episodes.name: The Robot
episodes.overview: Jon tests a cleaning robot.

episodes.name: Cat Nap
episodes.overview: Garfield and Odie watch a movie about a villain named Silent Jack and mistakenly believe Jon, with recent tooth surgery, to be Silent Jack. In the end Garfield, Odie and Squeak find out they were attacking Jon, but the real Silent Jack robs them.

episodes.name: Agent X
episodes.overview: Nermal finds a cat called "Agent X" who claims to be a Secret Agent, but really a runaway cat. Garfield becomes jealous as Agent X tells everyone about his adventures, so Garfield tries to prove he is a house cat named "Fluffykins".

episodes.name: A Game of Cat and Mouse
episodes.overview: Squeak and his family move in to Jon's house while Jon and Odie are out. Garfield allows Squeak's family to remain in the house on the condition that they be his servants. Jon comes back and Garfield has to remove Squeak and his family before Jon called Rat-Tator Pest, who's hefty bill would have meant that Jon would not be able to afford lasagna for years.

episodes.name: Perfect Pizza
episodes.overview: Garfield gets an awful tasting Pizza from Mama Meany's Pizza Palace, Vito's rival. Mama Meany is putting Vito out of business through coupons, contests and discounts and plans to expand the restaurant to take over Vito's. Garfield arranges for Eddie Gourmand to compare Mama Meany pizza with Vito's, bringing the closure of Mama Meany, and resumed success of Vito.

episodes.name: King Nermal
episodes.overview: Nermal lives with Garfield for 10 days because his owner is out of town. Nermal fakes a leg injury and Jon feels pity for Nermal, making Garfield and Odie do whatever he requests. Garfield and Odie get rid of him so they could enjoy their normal house and lives once again.

episodes.name: Desperately Seeking Pooky
episodes.overview: Garfield searches for his teddy bear Pooky after he is stolen by a dog named Hercules.

episodes.name: High Scale
episodes.overview: Jon and Liz put Garfield on a diet and force him to exercise when an electronic talking scale tells him that he's overweight.

episodes.name: Jon's Night Out
episodes.overview: Jon has difficulty sleeping, so a Hypnotist attempts to put Jon under hypnosis to make him fall asleep at the sound of a horn. However, Jon hears Odie's bark before the horn, making Odie the hypnosis trigger.

episodes.name: Not So Sweet Sound of Music
episodes.overview: Jon finds his old Accordion but Garfield doesn't like him playing it nor the very sound of it. Garfield tries to get rid of it, but in the end, the Accordion breaks and Jon gets bagpipes instead.

episodes.name: Turkey Trouble
episodes.overview: Jon wins a turkey in a competition, which he plans to cook for Liz. However, when it is delivered it is still alive. Garfield disguises himself as a turkey to get rid of the real one.

episodes.name: Pup in the Pound
episodes.overview: Odie gets taken to the dog pound as he's not wearing his license tag Collar. Garfield disguises himself as a dog to rescue Odie.

episodes.name: Odie in Love
episodes.overview: Odie falls in love with a shower brush. Garfield gets jealous as Odie is no longer paying attention to him and throws the brush in the recycling bin without Odie knowing it.

episodes.name: Pet Matchers
episodes.overview: Jon and Garfield fight so much against what to watch on TV that they decide to go on a TV show called Pet Matchers.

episodes.name: Lucky Charm
episodes.overview: Garfield gets rich after a Leprechaun gives him some good luck.

episodes.name: Curse of the Were-Dog
episodes.overview: Odie becomes a monster-dog in the middle of the night and eats a lasagna that was for for Jon and Liz. Jon thinks that Garfield is responsible, and blames him.

episodes.name: Meet the Parents
episodes.overview: Liz introduces Jon to her parents. Liz's father is a grumpy man, while Liz's mother has a canary named Petey - who Garfield tries to eat.

episodes.name: Down on the Farm
episodes.overview: Garfield goes to visit Jon's little brother Doc Boy. But with no TV and no pizza, Garfield shows the farm animals how to live life his way.

episodes.name: The Pet Show
episodes.overview: Garfield is rejected from The Pet Show because he's too fat to enter, so Odie takes his place and competes against Nermal for lasagna.

episodes.name: Curse of the Cat People
episodes.overview: Garfield and Odie get taken to another land through a magic mirror where Neferkitty (voiced by Susan Silo) and her Egyptian colony of cats live, planning their revenge on humans.

episodes.name: Glenda and Odessa
episodes.overview: Garfield and Odie are mistakenly accused of stealing barbecued ribs (really stolen by neighborhood pets) when they run away from Jon's twin girl cousins.

episodes.name: Underwater World
episodes.overview: Garfield and Odie discover talking fish in the sea.

episodes.name: Family Picture
episodes.overview: Jon tries to take the "perfect family picture" for Liz's birthday present but people always come and disturb everything.

episodes.name: Time Twist
episodes.overview: When an Alien stops at a Super-Market in earth, Garfield mistakenly enters his Space Ship and travels through different planets but it becomes hard for him to survive. The space ship and the alien are very similar to Doc Brown and the Flying DeLorean Time Machine from Back to the Future.

episodes.name: Time Master
episodes.overview: Garfield finds a Pocket watch which can stop time but panics when it breaks and time is frozen.

episodes.name: Fish to Fry
episodes.overview: When Jon reluctantly agrees to look after Liz's fish, Garfield can't resist eating them.

episodes.name: Little Yellow Riding Hood
episodes.overview: When Garfield, Jon, Odie, and Liz go on a picnic, Odie sneaks a baby wolf into the house and sends the Mom after Jon and Garfield.

episodes.name: Fame Fatale
episodes.overview: Garfield switches lives with a celebrity, Sir Leo, who is also Liz's cat claiming that the life of a super star is great. Sir Leo looks just like Garfield but speaks with a British accent. This is similar to Garfield: A Tail of Two Kitties.

episodes.name: Virtualodeon
episodes.overview: Garfield discovers a new 3-D format TV channel and ends up in the TV. Jon enlists the help of a scientist, Dr Bonkers, to help him get out. Meanwhile Garfield goes into commercials, a parade show, educational shows, cooking shows, game shows, and movies including Dr. No and Alien.

episodes.name: It's a Cat's World
episodes.overview: Garfield gets sucked into a parallel universe where cats act like humans and humans act like cats where he meets the human-like Garfield.

episodes.name: Mailman Blues
episodes.overview: Garfield torments Mailman Stu while Herman's on vacation in Hawaii.

episodes.name: Extreme Housebreaking
episodes.overview: Garfield is enrolled on the Dr. Whipple's Pet obedience course after Jon secretly tapes him misbehaving, but Garfield eventually discovers the doctor as a sham artist fraudulently using his course to launder money for himself; the doctor is then ruined when Garfield sneaks a microphone backstage as the Doctor says the public is stupid.

episodes.name: Heir Apparent
episodes.overview: Jon and Doc Boy might inherit their cousin's haunted estate but to take custody must stay there longer than the other.

episodes.name: From the Oven
episodes.overview: Jon is watching a cooking show to make Odie's birthday cake when Jon accidently switched the channel, leaving Jon to mistake the directions from the horror movie as being from the cooking show. It becomes a Frankenstein-like monster cake.

episodes.name: Caroling Capers
episodes.overview: After hearing children go door to door singing carols on TV, Garfield tries to go around singing carols for food, but all of his attempts are futile.

episodes.name: Neighbor Nathan
episodes.overview: Odie runs away from home, sick of Garfield's cruelty towards him, but the new house he runs off to is the residence of a boy with the personality of a mad scientist named Nathan, who plans to use his new invention to transform Odie into a cockroach. Now it is up to Garfield to save Odie.

episodes.name: History of Dog
episodes.overview: Garfield tells us about history of dogs, but puts them in a negative light. When Odie and his dog friends save Garfield's favorite Italian restaurant from a kitchen fire, Garfield is forced to admit that even dogs aren't that stupid.

episodes.name: Up a Tree
episodes.overview: Odie becomes friends with the garden squirrels after he helps one recover from an accident.

episodes.name: It's a Cheese World
episodes.overview: Garfield tries to take Squeak and his friends to Eddie Gormand's Cheeseland, but Harry is in charge of keeping mice out.

episodes.name: Nice to Nermal
episodes.overview: Nermal steals Pooky after Garfield is mean to him, and Garfield must be nice to Nermal to get Pooky back.

episodes.name: Out on a Limb
episodes.overview: Garfield, Odie, Nermal and Jon all get stuck in a tree, so they try to get help.

episodes.name: Super Me
episodes.overview: Garfield imitates a superhero so that Nermal will reward him with food, but gets caught up with the real superhero and a bank robbery.

episodes.name: Mastermind
episodes.overview: Garfield gets a device that reads people's minds and saves the world from Pizza-Craving Aliens.

episodes.name: The Amazing Flying Dog
episodes.overview: Odie dreams that he's a super-dog who can fly.

episodes.name: The Last Word
episodes.overview: Nermal bets Garfield he can't last an hour without eating.

episodes.name: Iceman
episodes.overview: Garfield helps Oga, the ice cream lady, find a prehistoric mate.

episodes.name: T3000
episodes.overview: After the dog catchers get fired for failing to stop Garfield and Odie from robbing a Deli, Garfield helps the dog catchers defeat the robotic dog catcher.

episodes.name: Home for the Holidays
episodes.overview: Garfield is looking forward to the holidays and all its joys. Arlene gives Garfield a reason to stop and remember the true meaning of the season, so Garfield decides to help some homeless Cats and Dogs by finding them homes.

episodes.name: Ticket to Riches
episodes.overview: Jon wins the lottery, but is unable to find his ticket.

episodes.name: Gravity of the Situation
episodes.overview: An alien from a planet with no gravity lands on earth to recharge his ship. While in Jon's house he cancels out gravity, causing household object to float around the house. This is Nimbus's second appearance, though he's been redesigned and has a higher pitched voice.

episodes.name: The Art of Being Uncute
episodes.overview: Eddie Gourmand is the judge for the Cutest Cat Of The Year award and decides for the new cute to be the opposite of cute, and the prize is six months in Greenland, so Garfield decides to make Nermal a mess in order to get some peace and quiet.

episodes.name: Night of the Bunny Slippers
episodes.overview: A pair of bunny slippers comes to life, and everyone must join forces to defeat them. This is Aunt Ivy's first appearance.

episodes.name: Blasteroid
episodes.overview: The Aliens previously seen in "Pasta Wars" send an asteroid made of meatballs to destroy Earth, Garfield and Odie reluctantly travel in a spaceship to stop the Blasteroid.

episodes.name: The Big Sneeze
episodes.overview: Jon sneezes every time he is near Garfield, and his doctor explains that he must get rid of Garfield, however when Garfield does something nice for Jon, he uncovers a shocking secret: he is allergic to goldenrod.

episodes.name: The Spy Who Fed Me
episodes.overview: Garfield has to lose ten pounds, but Jon discovers he has been snacking between meals. Liz gives him a robot that will follow Garfield everywhere he goes to endure he sticks to his diet, but Garfield tricks Jon

episodes.name: Meet Max Mouse
episodes.overview: Squeak's cat-hating relative, Max, moves into Garfield's home and rallies the other mice to rebel against him. Meanwhile, Jon calls an exterminator to come rid his house of them. This is Max's first appearance.

episodes.name: The Haunted House
episodes.overview: Jon spends the day in a vacation house to come up with a comic book idea. The only trouble is, the house is haunted.

episodes.name: Which Witch?
episodes.overview: The twins, Dresilla and Minerva, come to visit, and end up like Hansel and Gretal in an evil witch's lair.

episodes.name: Cyber Mailman
episodes.overview: The scientist Dr Bonkers creates a cyber mail man to deliver the post but some taco sauce falls into the central computer, making the cyber mail man deliver the next days news paper. Jon sees this as an opportunity to make money, using tomorrow's lottery numbers also printed in the paper. This episode has a parody of The Twilight Zone.

episodes.name: Odie for Sale
episodes.overview: Jon is in debt, and decides he must sell some of his possessions to pay the bill. When Garfield puts Odie on the stall for two cents, he is bought by the person Jon is being sued by, and it is up to Garfield to get him back.

episodes.name: Farm Fresh Feline
episodes.overview: Jon, Garfield, and Odie visit Doc Boy on the farm. While there, Dr. Whipple hypnotizes Garfield into doing farm work.

episodes.name: Dogs Day
episodes.overview: After Odie helps their friend, Nimbus the space alien, he gives him a forever doggie cookie. Odie licks Jon after eating it, and Jon starts acting like a dog. Then Jon licks Liz and the condition spreads.

episodes.name: Planet of Poultry
episodes.overview: Aliens from another planet plan to turn all the earth creatures into chickens. This is the first appearance of Vito's pizza boy.

episodes.name: With Four You Get Pizza
episodes.overview: Jon goes out on a date with Liz to Vito's Pizzaria and Garfield wants to go along, but Vito banned animals from entering the restaurant. So Garfield and Odie disguise themselves as Jon's "daughters" to get into Vito's, but Jon and Liz's date turns into disaster.

episodes.name: The Bluebird of Happiness
episodes.overview: One of the baby bluebirds from "Mother Garfield" return and Garfield saves him from Harry. But Nermal accidentally lets Harry have it and Garfield, Nermal, and Odie must save it.

episodes.name: Inside Eddie Gourmand
episodes.overview: After Eddie Gourmand gives a bad review about Vito's Pizzaria on TV, Jon, Garfield, and Odie go see him to find out why he's so cranky lately and help him reunite with his mother.

episodes.name: Fido Food Feline
episodes.overview: After eating dogfood, Garfield is convinced he's turning into a dog.

episodes.name: Everything's Relative
episodes.overview: Aunt Ivy's house is being rid of mice and she has to stay at Jon's home for a week. Then, Drusilla and Minerva show up, and Jon is so annoyed with them that he tries to get them to stay at Doc Boy's farm. But Doc Boy doesn't want to put up with them either. This is Aunt Esther, Lucretia, and Tabitha's first appearance.

episodes.name: Honey, I Shrunk the Pets
episodes.overview: Nathan returns and shrinks Garfield with his shrink ray, and Garfield must find a way to return to normal size.

episodes.name: Garfield Astray
episodes.overview: After Garfield plays a mean trick on Nermal, a bowling ball falls on his head and loses his memory. Then, Nermal tricks Garfield into thinking he's a stray cat named Ichabod. Then Garfield meets a couple of stray cats named Tino and Gino. This is Tino and Gino's first appearance.

episodes.name: History of Cats
episodes.overview: Garfield tells a small yet untrue history about his own species, and the mice are upset because Garfield is making it seem as though cats actually did everything in history.

episodes.name: Black Cat Blues
episodes.overview: A miserable, black cat named Jonah passes by Garfield outside, and Garfield is given a curse and has bad luck all the time. Garfield must figure out how to lift the curse.

episodes.name: Cuter Than Cute
episodes.overview: Nermal comes over for a visit and the space lasagna return once again and send a spy disguised as a cute kitten over to Garfield's home. The "kitten" is way cuter than Nermal, and Nermal gets jealous.

episodes.name: Great Pizza Race
episodes.overview: Jon goes out on a big date with Liz and orders Garfield a pizza for dinner from Vito's Pizzaria. Garfield uses a tape recorder to record Jon's ordering the pizza, and uses it to get free pizza and, also, to harass Vito.

episodes.name: The Guest from Beyond
episodes.overview: Eddie Gourmand, a food critic, is fired from his show only to be replaced by his station manager who wants to promote a healthier way of cooking. After a chance meeting in a movie theater, Jon invites him back to his house for dinner. But when Eddie injures his foot because of Garfield, he has to stay at Jonâs and orders him to take care of him until he is healed or else heâll sue.

episodes.name: A Gripping Tale
episodes.overview: Odie gets captured by a giant squid in the sewer and Garfield attempts to rescue him

episodes.name: Full of Beans
episodes.overview: Odie accidently swallows a mexican jumping bean

episodes.name: Love and Lasagna
episodes.overview: Vito is sad after Angeluca broke up with him.

episodes.name: True Colors
episodes.overview: The TV in the living room needs to be fixed. While it is away Jon brings out his old TV. Jon shows Garfield a show he used to like when he was a kid. Garfield watches the show, but he keeps complaining because there is no color. The TV shockingly speaks back and takes away Garfield's colors until he becomes nice enough to get them back. After he has done his good deeds he goes back to the house and finds the the TV is back and the old one is put back in storage. Garfield is glad he did good deeds and returns to watching colored television.

episodes.name: Unfair Weather
episodes.overview: Jon, Garfield, Odie, Drusilla and Minerva discover some strange weather when going camping

episodes.name: Furry Tales
episodes.overview: Garfield tells Odie a fairy tale about a prince.

episodes.name: Kind to Kittens
episodes.overview: The mayor passes a law requiring everyone to be kind to cats.

episodes.name: Little Angel
episodes.overview: Jon adopts a kitten who is more trouble than he's worth.

episodes.name: Prehistoric Pup
episodes.overview: After a meteorite lands, it turns Odie into a prehistoric dog.

episodes.name: Land of Later
episodes.overview: A group of inhabitants who live underground turn everbody into procrastinators.

episodes.name: Laugh in a Can
episodes.overview: The network adds a laugh track to Garfield's show, much to his chagrin.

episodes.name: The Non-Garfield Show
episodes.overview: Jon pitches an idea for a TV show to a successful producer.

episodes.name: The Caped Avenger Rides Again!
episodes.overview: Garfield solves a mystery of who stole a rare comic book.

episodes.name: The Superhero Apprentice
episodes.overview: Nermal becomes a supervillain to get revenge on Garfield's Caped Avenger routine.

episodes.name: Teddy Dearest
episodes.overview: Jon sells Pooky as a new toy to Mr. Allwork.

episodes.name: Bath Day
episodes.overview: Garfield, Odie, and Nermal have a fantasy while in the bathtub.

episodes.name: What a Difference a Pet Makes
episodes.overview: Garfield answers fan mail sent in asking about pets.

episodes.name: Garfield Gets Canned
episodes.overview: Garfield tries to open a can of food while Jon is away for a while.

episodes.name: Partners in Mime
episodes.overview: Jon takes part in a competition for mimes.

episodes.name: Boris the Snowman
episodes.overview: While vacationing, Garfield encounters a couple of snowmen who come to life.

episodes.name: Long Lost Lyman
episodes.overview: Jon, Garfield, and Odie go in search of their friend Lyman.

episodes.name: Cupid Cat
episodes.overview: Jon tries to help his brother Doc Boy find a companion.

episodes.name: The Control Freak
episodes.overview: Nathan tests a out device that can control people's minds.

episodes.name: Every Witch Way
episodes.overview: Mrs. Cauldron's niece wants to marry Jon.

episodes.name: Revenge of the Cat People
episodes.overview: Neferkitty (or Fuzzbutton) turns everybody in town to stone.

episodes.name: Filthy Figitives
episodes.overview: Garfield decides to fire all the other characters.

episodes.name: Smartest Dog in the World
episodes.overview: Doc Boy takes his farm animals to Jon's house for him to look after.

episodes.name: More than Meets the Eye
episodes.overview: Mrs. Cauldron casts a spell on Odie that makes him smarter.

episodes.name: Fast Friends
episodes.overview: Garfield tries to become faster than Mrs. Ferret.

episodes.name: Where's Odie
episodes.overview: Jon gives out a cash reward to whoever gives Garfield and Odie a bath.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Machine
episodes.overview: Nathan tests out a device that can make one invisible.
